The paper focuses on sorting problems related to strings and suffixes, which are fundamental data structures in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses parallelization techniques, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of external memory algorithms suggests cs.DB (Databases), while the application of sorting to high-dimensional geometric data could relate to cs.PL (Computational Geometry). Finally, the use of a new distributed big data framework named Thrill could fall under cs.PF (Performance).
